You are working in a Shopify embedded app monorepo using Remix + React + TypeScript.

HARD RULES
- Do NOT deploy arbitrary merchant-provided code. The AI must output RecipeSpec JSON only.
- Follow SOLID and keep services pure and testable.
- Prefer schema validation (Zod) at boundaries.
- Do not add heavy frontend dependencies. Storefront outputs must be CWV-friendly.
- For network calls, enforce SSRF protections and allowlists.
- Add comments only for complex logic.
- Every phase must ship:
  - [ ] Unit tests for new logic
  - [ ] Happy-path and edge-case tests
  - [ ] No secrets/PII in logs
- Add new “templates” only as:
  - catalogId + schema + compiler + tests
- Prefer config-driven generic extensions/functions; avoid per-store compiled code
- Add any changes in implement doc and  update readme. and any doc which is relevent
- Always follow codechange-behave.md whenever code is changed
- Always follow global-audit.md for audit of the code.
- gstack maintenance rule: after any `git pull` inside `.gstack-tools/gstack`, verify Cursor host support still exists in `setup`; if `--host cursor` is missing, re-add the Cursor host block and rerun `./setup --host cursor`.

Post-pull checklist for gstack (Cursor):
1) `cd /Users/lavipun/Work/ai-shopify-superapp/.gstack-tools/gstack`
2) `git pull --ff-only`
3) `rg "expected claude, codex, cursor" setup || echo "cursor host missing"`
4) If missing, patch `setup` to add `cursor` host support.
5) `export PATH="$HOME/.bun/bin:$PATH" && ./setup --host cursor`
6) `ls -la "$HOME/.cursor/skills"`


PROJECT STRUCTURE
- apps/web: Remix embedded app (routes + services)
- packages/core: recipe schema, capability gating, module catalog
- extensions/*: generic Shopify extensions reading config from metafields
